Sentencas: In order to improve the electrochemical performance of the LaBaCuCoO5+delta (LBCC) electrode, LaBaCuCoO5+delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (LBCC-SDC) are prepared and characterized for potential application as a cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) based on an SDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of LaBaCuCoO5+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and electrochemical properties are investigated by four probing DC technique, dilatometry, AC impedance and polarization techniques, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of LaBaCuCoO5+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that the thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) and electrical conductivity decrease with the increase of SDC content in LBCC-SDC composites.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of LaBaCuCoO5+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: AC impedance spectra based on SDC electrolyte measured at intermediate temperatures show that the addition of SDC to LBCC improves the electrochemical performance of a LBCC cathode, and that a LBCC-SDC20 cathode exhibits superior electrochemical performance in the LBCC-SDCx composite cathodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of LaBaCuCoO5+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, even when the content of SDC is up to 40 wt%, the area specific resistance of the LBCC-SDC40 composite cathode on SDC electrolyte is lower than the corresponding interfacial resistance for pure LBCC at 650-800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of LaBaCuCoO5+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The power density of the Ni-SDC/SDC/LBCC-SDC20 cell is 615 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of LaBaCuCoO5+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that LBCC-SDCx is a potential cathode material for application in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical characterization of LaBaCuCoO5+δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
